Open the watertight doors.

509
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:24,766
Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

510
00:40:24,939 --> 00:40:27,641
If you're ready for breakfast, sir,
I'll be in the wardroom.

511
00:40:27,855 --> 00:40:29,728
What is that?
- Orange juice, sir.

512
00:40:29,898 --> 00:40:30,928
Where are you taking it?

513
00:40:31,106 --> 00:40:33,560
For Mr. Holden. He's
having breakfast in bed.

514
00:40:34,524 --> 00:40:36,561
Wait a moment, Sgt.

515
00:40:37,150 --> 00:40:39,271
I'll take it down.
- Yes, sir.

516
00:40:45,526 --> 00:40:47,066
May I come in?

517
00:40:49,403 --> 00:40:50,432
Please do.

518
00:40:50,610 --> 00:40:52,435
Good morning.
- Good morning, Mr. Holden.

519
00:40:52,610 --> 00:40:55,562
I've got a bad neck from too much tennis.
- Really?

520
00:40:56,570 --> 00:40:58,313
Well. Did you get a good night's sleep?

521
00:40:58,779 --> 00:41:01,611
Not too good; it was a little damp
and noisy. Strange surroundings.

522
00:41:01,779 --> 00:41:03,238
I'm sorry to hear that.

523
00:41:03,904 --> 00:41:04,935
Thank you.

524
00:41:05,114 --> 00:41:07,022
Well, how's the food?
Satisfactory?

525
00:41:07,572 --> 00:41:09,231
Excellent, thank you.

526
00:41:09,447 --> 00:41:11,734
Would you like a cigar?
- No, no thanks.

527
00:41:12,990 --> 00:41:15,029
I suppose after you
digested breakfast...

528
00:41:15,199 --> 00:41:17,984
you'll want to get up on deck and play
a little shuffleboard, right?

529
00:41:21,658 --> 00:41:25,026
This war must be inconvenient
for you, Mr. Holden?

530
00:41:25,244 --> 00:41:26,901
I try to make the best of.

531
00:41:27,076 --> 00:41:30,277
Yes, and you do, indeed you do.

532
00:41:30,827 --> 00:41:33,944
I know you're not familiar with
the way the functions at sea.

533
00:41:34,119 --> 00:41:36,027
Cigarette?
- No, thank you.

534
00:41:36,995 --> 00:41:39,152
But here we all...

535
00:41:39,662 --> 00:41:41,949
We all eat and work together... ...

536
00:41:42,121 --> 00:41:45,535
and so you won't upset that system,
You will have to do it our way.

537
00:41:46,163 --> 00:41:49,115
You've got three minutes to get off
your fat mattress...

538
00:41:49,289 --> 00:41:51,327
and report to Mr. Watson!
- Yes, sir.

539
00:41:51,498 --> 00:41:54,781
You are going to learn something
if I have to poor it into you!

540
00:41:54,957 --> 00:41:58,999
Another thing : here we dress alike,
Got any regulation trousers?

541
00:41:59,166 --> 00:42:02,250
No, sir. I had all my clothes made
at " Saks " Fifth Avenue.

542
00:42:02,417 --> 00:42:05,037
I can't to do anything about the
uniform, but don't want you to think...

543
00:42:05,211 --> 00:42:08,076
I'll expect breakfast
in bed every morning.

544
00:42:09,169 --> 00:42:11,538
Scuttlebutt is that we will
submerge at daybreak...

545
00:42:11,710 --> 00:42:13,784
... and if you gotta go,
you might as well go big.

546
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:17,409
It is past daybreak
and we are submerged.

547
00:42:19,088 --> 00:42:20,876
We are?
- Yes.

548
00:42:22,213 --> 00:42:23,920
You mean we're under??
- Yes

549
00:42:27,338 --> 00:42:29,459
But it isn't a permanent
situation?

550
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,836
I mean, we can
up if we'd like to?

551
00:42:32,007 --> 00:42:35,290
Well, I'd like to think we can.
But I'm an incurable optimist.

552
00:42:38,008 --> 00:42:39,880
What happens, sir, if... ?

553
00:42:40,301 --> 00:42:42,337
What happens if we can not... ?

554
00:42:44,884 --> 00:42:46,376
If we can not...

555
00:42:46,550 --> 00:42:47,748
Then...

556
00:42:49,759 --> 00:42:53,007
What kind of answer is that?
- Why? Nervous, Mr. Holden?

557
00:42:53,469 --> 00:42:54,583
Yes.

558
00:42:55,136 --> 00:42:57,885
Tell me something :
Why did you join the navy?

559
00:42:58,512 --> 00:43:00,633
because I needed
an officer's uniform.

560
00:43:01,345 --> 00:43:04,675
As a kid I was a victim of the
most vicious propaganda;...

561
00:43:04,845 --> 00:43:07,845
people told me... that money
was not everything, and I believed it.

562
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:10,256
Until I found out that
people saying...

563
00:43:10,431 --> 00:43:12,717
... "money is not everything "
were the ones who had it.

564
00:43:12,889 --> 00:43:15,426
I figured they were trying
to hide a good thing.

565
00:43:15,848 --> 00:43:17,127
Sir, please sit down.

566
00:43:17,724 --> 00:43:18,802
Yes.

567
00:43:22,267 --> 00:43:25,135
Now there are two simple
ways to make money :. .

568
00:43:25,308 --> 00:43:27,429
You can steal it,
or you can marry it.

569
00:43:28,060 --> 00:43:31,012
To marry it, you have to
travel in the right circles...

570
00:43:31,186 --> 00:43:32,761
... on the right side of the tracks.

571
00:43:32,936 --> 00:43:34,014
Two things I learned:

572
00:43:34,186 --> 00:43:37,516
One : A uniform can take you
to the best places, and two :. .

573
00:43:37,770 --> 00:43:40,852
no one ever checks Dun and
Bradstreet in a bedroom.

574
00:43:41,230 --> 00:43:43,220
It sounds like a
winning combination.

575
00:43:43,395 --> 00:43:44,889
Would you like to see the jackpot?

576
00:43:46,687 --> 00:43:49,355
That the girl from
the right side of the tracks?

577
00:43:49,897 --> 00:43:51,306
She owns the tracks...

578
00:43:51,563 --> 00:43:55,724
... or 5. 2 % of all the
railroad stock in America.

579
00:43:56,481 --> 00:43:57,596
Isn't she lovely?

580
00:43:58,066 --> 00:44:02,013
We had a dinner date one night, and
I was a few minutes late...

581
00:44:02,192 --> 00:44:03,732
and she didn't want it to happen again.

582
00:44:04,899 --> 00:44:07,269
Have you ever seen
a two thousand dollar watch?

583
00:44:07,483 --> 00:44:08,811
My, my, my.

584
00:44:09,443 --> 00:44:13,105
When the minister says " will you take
this woman? " he won't be kidding.

585
00:44:13,944 --> 00:44:16,694
When is the happy occasion?
- The day I get back.

586
00:44:17,277 --> 00:44:20,727
You see that I get back and I'll
see you have a private submarine.

587
00:44:20,904 --> 00:44:22,101
For heaven's sake.

588
00:44:27,488 --> 00:44:29,029
Excuse me.

589
00:44:29,363 --> 00:44:32,065
Is this normal or should
I be nervous again?

590
00:44:32,238 --> 00:44:33,945
Captain!
- Yes

591
00:44:34,115 --> 00:44:36,153
One of our connections
carried away, sir...

592
00:44:36,323 --> 00:44:38,480
We're rigging a patch,
but I don't think it will hold.

593
00:44:40,616 --> 00:44:43,779
Prepare to surface.
- Stand by to surface. Lookouts to conning tower.

594
00:44:43,950 --> 00:44:45,229
Stand by to surface.
Lookouts to conning tower.

595
00:44:45,408 --> 00:44:47,612
How much time for repairs?
- About six hours...

596
00:44:47,783 --> 00:44:49,989
... if we can work over the side.
- Six hours...

597
00:44:50,575 --> 00:44:54,156
The nearest place with a
sheltered anchorage is

598
00:44:54,326 --> 00:44:55,904
Marinduque island. We better head there.
- Okay.

599
00:44:56,078 --> 00:44:57,108
Watch your fault.
- Yes, sir.

600
00:44:57,285 --> 00:44:59,242
All free, sir. Sound the alarm.

601
00:45:01,620 --> 00:45:04,026
22 December, 1941.

602
00:45:04,244 --> 00:45:07,825
Arrived Marinduque two hours
after enemy air raid.

603
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:11,197
Repairs have to be completed
before their next visit.

604
00:45:11,372 --> 00:45:13,577
To get Lt. Holden out
from underfoot...

605
00:45:13,747 --> 00:45:17,362
I sent him and his men
to scout the island.

606
00:45:22,332 --> 00:45:24,157
Captain.
- Yes

607
00:45:24,916 --> 00:45:26,493
Mr. Holden is coming back, sir.

608
00:45:26,667 --> 00:45:29,416
War is hell,
Mr. Watson.

609
00:45:30,585 --> 00:45:32,659
Not only that, sir.

610
00:45:33,501 --> 00:45:35,244
Wait until you see
what he's got with him.

611
00:46:00,257 --> 00:46:01,169
Women!

612
00:46:01,424 --> 00:46:04,505
Wow! That's what
I call scavenging!

613
00:46:06,967 --> 00:46:08,756
I... What I meant sir is...

614
00:46:08,926 --> 00:46:11,794
... I'm sure there will be something
they can be used for.

615
00:46:12,051 --> 00:46:15,215
I can think of many uses,
but not here and now.

616
00:46:15,761 --> 00:46:19,921
Mr. Stovall, the influence of
Lt. Holden is beginning to worry me.

617
00:46:20,094 --> 00:46:23,424
I suggest you "Wow!" less and
"Tsk Tsk Tsk" more...

618
00:46:44,557 --> 00:46:46,928
Mayor Heywood.
- Major Heywood.

619
00:46:49,183 --> 00:46:51,554
Lieutenant Duran.
- Lieutenant Duran.

620
00:46:53,310 --> 00:46:55,466
Lieutenant Reid.
- Lieutenant.

621
00:46:57,227 --> 00:46:58,768
Lieutenant. Colfax.

622
00:46:59,728 --> 00:47:00,757
Lieutenant.

623
00:47:02,644 --> 00:47:04,186
Lieutenant Crandall.

624
00:47:07,395 --> 00:47:09,885
If anyone asks what
you're fighting for...

625
00:47:10,521 --> 00:47:11,849
... there's your answer.

626
00:47:16,689 --> 00:47:19,356
Lt. Holden invited us
to go with you.

627
00:47:19,648 --> 00:47:20,560
What?

628
00:47:20,773 --> 00:47:22,978
The Major and her unit
were stranded, sir.

629
00:47:23,148 --> 00:47:25,519
We were en route to Manila
and heard it was being bombed...

630
00:47:25,691 --> 00:47:27,932
... and we had to land here.
- Oh.

631
00:47:28,108 --> 00:47:30,313
The Japanese strafed
the airstrip and...

632
00:47:30,484 --> 00:47:33,054
our plane took off to keep from
being destroyed on the ground.

633
00:47:33,233 --> 00:47:34,693
He was supposed to
come back for us.

634
00:47:34,860 --> 00:47:36,269
Alright.
- it didn't make it.

635
00:47:36,443 --> 00:47:39,276
They were the only Americans
on the island, sir...

636
00:47:39,443 --> 00:47:41,350
You could not possibly
leave them there.

637
00:47:41,611 --> 00:47:42,559
Thank you.

638
00:47:42,820 --> 00:47:45,902
It's an emergency, sir.
- Thank you, Mr. Holden.

639
00:47:46,612 --> 00:47:50,820
Now, Major, obviously we have to
get out of here as fast as we can, so...

640
00:47:51,279 --> 00:47:53,947
if you'll get your party below,
I'll get you to Cebu...

641
00:47:54,113 --> 00:47:55,940
... where you can
rejoin an Army unit.

642
00:47:56,155 --> 00:47:59,238
Escort the Major to the wardroom.
- Yes, sir.

643
00:47:59,407 --> 00:48:00,271
Thank you, Lieutenant.

644
00:48:00,448 --> 00:48:02,403
Thank you, ma'am.
- This way, ladies.

645
00:48:07,116 --> 00:48:09,238
I guess I'm stuck.
- Yes

646
00:48:09,408 --> 00:48:12,490
Just a minute. Come on. That's right.

647
00:48:13,659 --> 00:48:16,528
Thank you very much.
- Suggest you take the other one off.

648
00:48:23,828 --> 00:48:24,858
Sir.

649
00:48:25,327 --> 00:48:26,572
Mr. Holden, just a minute.

650
00:48:26,745 --> 00:48:28,985
Mr. Watson!
- Yes, sir?

651
00:48:30,538 --> 00:48:32,030
Please assemble the crew.

652
00:48:32,246 --> 00:48:35,992
Instruct them to ignore that
our passengers are women.

653
00:48:36,289 --> 00:48:37,866
That may require some...

654
00:48:38,039 --> 00:48:41,404
readjustment... but I want
every man to understand...

655
00:48:41,580 --> 00:48:43,786
our objective is Cebu
and then Darwin.

656
00:48:44,081 --> 00:48:46,619
If any man has any
other objective in mind...

657
00:48:46,833 --> 00:48:48,159
he'd better forget it.

658
00:48:48,332 --> 00:48:50,075
You will put on report...

659
00:48:50,499 --> 00:48:51,780
Collision!

660
00:48:53,458 --> 00:48:55,284
Collision, sir!
- Really...

661
00:48:55,460 --> 00:48:57,118
we're not even moving.

662
00:49:03,877 --> 00:49:06,081
Who hit the collision button?
- I do not know, sir.

663
00:49:06,252 --> 00:49:09,501
Everything has a reason
for being here...

664
00:49:10,629 --> 00:49:12,667
What happened?
- I'm very sorry.

665
00:49:12,838 --> 00:49:16,454
I was coming down the ladder and
accidentally touched that button.

666
00:49:16,455 --> 00:49:17,454
She grabbed the collision alarm.

667
00:49:17,455 --> 00:49:18,123
Just a minute.

668
00:49:18,962 --> 00:49:22,128
Please, ladies, there is one primary rule
you must observe:. .

669
00:49:22,298 --> 00:49:24,621
keep your hands...
and... you're, uh...

670
00:49:25,005 --> 00:49:27,045
Just do not touch anything.

671
00:49:27,257 --> 00:49:31,122
The ladies will occupy the Chief's quarters
and my cabin.

672
00:49:31,300 --> 00:49:35,591
The Chiefs move out with the men. Move my gear
with Watson and you stay with Holden.

673
00:49:36,343 --> 00:49:37,587
Now, uh...

674
00:49:38,634 --> 00:49:41,882
For the next few days we'll
be living in close contact...

675
00:49:42,052 --> 00:49:43,675
and you being women... and...

676
00:49:43,844 --> 00:49:48,004
the crew being men,
being confined could...

677
00:49:48,763 --> 00:49:51,132
could create situations...
not usually...

678
00:49:51,303 --> 00:49:53,710
consistent with normal
submarine operations.

679
00:49:55,180 --> 00:49:57,503
What I mean to say.
- We know what you mean, Captain.

680
00:49:57,681 --> 00:49:59,552
We're well acquainted
with the facts of life.

681
00:49:59,722 --> 00:50:03,052
So are the men. I'm just trying to
avoid any exchange of information.

682
00:50:05,973 --> 00:50:07,135
You must...

683
00:50:07,766 --> 00:50:09,092
You must realize that...

684
00:50:09,265 --> 00:50:12,468
submarines are not designed
to be coeducational.

685
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:13,840
... That is to say...

686
00:50:16,184 --> 00:50:19,265
Mr. Stovall, take the
ladies to the wardroom.

687
00:50:19,435 --> 00:50:21,805
I'll try to work out a schedule.
- Yes, sir.

688
00:50:25,353 --> 00:50:27,094
You'll eat in the officers' mess.

689
00:50:27,811 --> 00:50:32,101
Mealtimes are
7:00, 12:00 and 18:00.

690
00:50:33,271 --> 00:50:35,428
Now, this is the shower.

691
00:50:35,605 --> 00:50:36,387
Excuse me.

692
00:50:37,230 --> 00:50:39,138
Instructions are on the bulkhead.

693
00:50:39,396 --> 00:50:42,844
Your shower period
will be 6:30 to 6:50.

694
00:50:43,106 --> 00:50:45,310
You will each have
a minute and a half.

695
00:50:45,481 --> 00:50:46,808
A minute and a half?

696
00:50:47,399 --> 00:50:50,397
Captain 's orders, there are
problems with fresh water supply.

697
00:50:50,566 --> 00:50:52,224
How can you shower in
a minute and a half?

698
00:50:52,399 --> 00:50:55,233
What you miss one day you
can get the next time around.

699
00:50:55,692 --> 00:50:59,188
In here is what we
in the Navy call...

700
00:51:02,442 --> 00:51:05,014
It's operated by means of
the air compression levers...

701
00:51:05,193 --> 00:51:07,812
What do they call it?

702
00:51:09,278 --> 00:51:12,230
The head.

703
00:51:13,446 --> 00:51:17,654
I've drawn a complete diagram.
I'm sure you will have no trouble.

704
00:51:27,408 --> 00:51:29,196
Why do they call it the head?

705
00:51:30,325 --> 00:51:31,522
Doesn't say.

706
00:51:33,618 --> 00:51:35,820
A woman on board
is bad luck, sir...

707
00:51:35,991 --> 00:51:38,279
... and if one is bad luck,
imagine five.

708
00:51:38,451 --> 00:51:41,532
Alright, what do you want me to do?
Throw them overboard?

709
00:51:41,744 --> 00:51:43,366
It 's something to think about.

710
00:51:46,453 --> 00:51:48,408
Do what you can, okay?

711
00:51:50,079 --> 00:51:51,620
Hunkle, what 's going
on in there?

712
00:51:51,787 --> 00:51:53,777
It's a raffle, they're
drawing for the women.

713
00:51:53,953 --> 00:51:55,032
They're drawing for the women?

714
00:51:55,204 --> 00:51:58,155
Mr. Holden organized it. They're
picking the five lucky men now.

715
00:52:00,330 --> 00:52:01,278
Kraus.

716
00:52:02,873 --> 00:52:05,824
Congratulations.
What did you give away?

717
00:52:05,998 --> 00:52:07,575
What's going on?
- A raffle, sir.

718
00:52:07,748 --> 00:52:08,911
What kind of raffle?

719
00:52:09,082 --> 00:52:12,200
For clothing.
- Clothes?

720
00:52:12,375 --> 00:52:14,615
Yes. The men are donating
their clothes to the women.

721
00:52:15,167 --> 00:52:17,157
Have you men finished chow?
- Yes, sir.

722
00:52:17,333 --> 00:52:20,284
Then back on the job. We
have to get out of here.

723
00:52:20,917 --> 00:52:22,327
Mr. Holden.
- Yes, sir.

724
00:52:25,710 --> 00:52:27,701
How did all that get started?

725
00:52:28,044 --> 00:52:30,535
I thought I was boosting
the men's morale, sir...

726
00:52:30,712 --> 00:52:32,868
... after all there's a practical side ;...

727
00:52:33,045 --> 00:52:35,367
these women have been
on an island for quite a while...

728
00:52:35,546 --> 00:52:37,203
